  <original-body>For some values, the helper method &quot;number_to_human_size&quot; gives a wrong result. See this examples:

Correct:
&lt;pre&gt;
number_to_human_size(41500, :precision =&gt; 0)
=&gt; &quot;41 KB&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;

Wrong:
&lt;pre&gt;
number_to_human_size(41100, :precision =&gt; 0)
=&gt; &quot;4 KB&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;

My Environment:
* ruby 1.8.6 (2007-09-24 patchlevel 111) [i686-darwin9.1.0]
* Rails 2.2.2</original-body>
